dvbInaIf.description: The MIB modules for INAs that conform to the EuroModem specification. This MIB assumes the INA implements MIB-II RFC 1213 The original MIB definition work was carried out for the DVB-RC group by Bert Van Willigen Philips Research Laboratory Eindhoven, The Netherlands.

MacFlagSet.name: MacFlagSet
MacFlagSet.description: This data type represents a reference to a set of MAC Flags. This reference is used in different MAC messages. See also ES 200 800, section 5.3.1.3.

EtsTimeOut.name: EtsTimeOut
EtsTimeOut.description: This data type represents possible timeout values. See also ES 200 800, section 5.5.3.2.

Modulation.name: Modulation
Modulation.description: Modulation type: OOB: qpsk(1) IB : qpsk(1), qam16(2), qam32(3), qam64(4), qam128(5), qam256(6)

DownstreamSymbolrate.name: DownstreamSymbolrate
DownstreamSymbolrate.description: The downstream transmission symbol rate used in symbol/s The symbol rate is given as an integer. Commonly used symbolrates are : symbol/s --------------------------------------- 6800000 IB 8Mhz 6875000 IB 8Mhz 6900000 IB 8Mhz 4896000 IB 6Mhz 5168000 IB 6Mhz 5304000 IB 6Mhz 772000 OOB optional, Grade A 1544000 OOB mandatory, Grade B

UpstreamSymbolrate.name: UpstreamSymbolrate
UpstreamSymbolrate.description: The upstream transmission symbol rate used. symbol/s --------------------------------- sr0128000 optional Grade A sr0772000 optional Grade B sr1544000 mandatory Grade C sr3088000 optional Grade D

dvbInaIfMacTable.name: dvbInaIfMacTable
dvbInaIfMacTable.description: Describes the attributes of each MAC interface, extending the information available from ifEntry.

dvbInaIfMacEntry.name: dvbInaIfMacEntry
dvbInaIfMacEntry.description: An entry containing objects describing attributes of each MAC entry, extending the information in ifEntry. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of dvbRecMacLayer(146). The state of the MAC depends on the state of the INA. If the INA is not operational also the MAC is not operational.

dvbInaIfMacDeviceCapabilities.name: dvbInaIfMacDeviceCapabilities
dvbInaIfMacDeviceCapabilities.description: This 32-bit object specifies the maximum capabilities of this MAC entity. This is the possible set of capability for this INA.

dvbInaIfMacDeviceExtendedCapabilities.name: dvbInaIfMacDeviceExtendedCapabilities
dvbInaIfMacDeviceExtendedCapabilities.description: This 32-bit object specifies the maximum extended capabilities of this MAC entity. This is the possible set of capability for this INA.

dvbInaIfMacCapabilities.name: dvbInaIfMacCapabilities
dvbInaIfMacCapabilities.description: This 32-bit object specifies the capabilities of this MAC entity. It is equal to or a subset of dvbInaIfMacDeviceCapabilities. Default this parameter is equal to dvbInaIfMacDeviceCapabilities. The object can be used to restrict the capabilities for this MAC entity.

dvbInaIfMacExtendedCapabilities.name: dvbInaIfMacExtendedCapabilities
dvbInaIfMacExtendedCapabilities.description: This 32-bit object specifies the extended capabilities of this MAC entity. It is equal to or a subset of dvbInaIfMacDeviceExtendedCapabilities. Default this parameter is equal to dvbInaIfMacDeviceExtendedCapabilities. The object can be used to restrict the extended capabilities for this MAC entity.

dvbInaIfMacProtocolSupport.name: dvbInaIfMacProtocolSupport
dvbInaIfMacProtocolSupport.description: Specifies the MAC standard version supported by this MAC entity. Optional, this parameter can be written to force a particular MAC version to be executed by the INA.

dvbInaIfMacTimeoutD.name: dvbInaIfMacTimeoutD
dvbInaIfMacTimeoutD.description: Time-out value 0xD. Terminal Time-Out, Security Sign-On.

dvbInaIfMacTimeoutE.name: dvbInaIfMacTimeoutE
dvbInaIfMacTimeoutE.description: Time-out value 0xE. Terminal Time-Out, Main Key Exchange.

dvbInaIfMacTimeoutF.name: dvbInaIfMacTimeoutF
dvbInaIfMacTimeoutF.description: Time-out value 0xF. Terminal Time-Out, Quick/Explicit Key exchange.

dvbInaIfMacRapidSignOnEnable.name: dvbInaIfMacRapidSignOnEnable
dvbInaIfMacRapidSignOnEnable.description: This Boolean parameter specifies whether the NIU's are allowed to do a rapid sign-on when they enter the sign-on process. (See the Need_Calibration bit in the <MAC> Sign-On_Request_Message.). By default this object is False.

dvbInaIfMacRespCollTimeWindow.name: dvbInaIfMacRespCollTimeWindow
dvbInaIfMacRespCollTimeWindow.description: Specifies the maximum time for the sign-on response message transmission randomisation.

dvbInaIfMacAddressFilterUse.name: dvbInaIfMacAddressFilterUse
dvbInaIfMacAddressFilterUse.description: This setting controls the use of the of the Address filter in the Sign-On Request Message. Disabled : The address filter is not used. Managed : The manager can control the use of the address filter with dvbInaIfMacAddressPositionMask and dvbInaIfMacAddressComparisonValue Automatic : The INA controls use of the address filter itself. The readback values of dvbInaIfMacAddressPositionMask and dvbInaIfMacAddressComparisonValue will not necessary reflect the values used by the INA.

dvbInaIfMacAddressPositionMask.name: dvbInaIfMacAddressPositionMask
dvbInaIfMacAddressPositionMask.description: Indicates the bit positions in the NIU MAC address that are used for address filtering comparison.

dvbInaIfMacAddressComparisonValue.name: dvbInaIfMacAddressComparisonValue
dvbInaIfMacAddressComparisonValue.description: Specifies the value that the NIU should use for MAC address comparison.

dvbInaIfMacGrantProtocolTimeOut.name: dvbInaIfMacGrantProtocolTimeOut
dvbInaIfMacGrantProtocolTimeOut.description: Default value for the time that the NIU should wait before verifying the status of pending grants. See also dvbInaIfNiuGrantProtocolTimeOut.

dvbInaIfMacIdleInterval.name: dvbInaIfMacIdleInterval
dvbInaIfMacIdleInterval.description: Specifies the transmission interval in seconds to be used for the MAC Idle message. When this value is zero, no idle messages shall be sent.

dvbInaIfMacIdleInvalidCount.name: dvbInaIfMacIdleInvalidCount
dvbInaIfMacIdleInvalidCount.description: Specifies a MAC Idle message invalid period in number of dvbInaIfMacIdleInterval, after which the NIU is declared to be signed-off. For example, if dvbInaIfMacIdleInterval is 5 seconds and this parameter is 3, then if in 15 seconds no data and/or MAC Idle messages are received, the INA will assume that the NIU in question has signed-off. This object is only valid when dvbInaIfMacIdleInterval is non-zero.

dvbInaIfMacN.name: dvbInaIfMacN
dvbInaIfMacN.description: Maximum value of the upstream slot position register.

dvbInaIfMacMaxContentionMsgLen.name: dvbInaIfMacMaxContentionMsgLen
dvbInaIfMacMaxContentionMsgLen.description: The default value for the Maximum_Contention_Access_Message_Length in the Connect Message. This is the maximum length of a message that may be transmitted using contention access. Any message greater than this should use reservation access. See also dvbInaIfConMaxContentionMsgLen.

dvbInaIfMacMaxReservationMsgLen.name: dvbInaIfMacMaxReservationMsgLen
dvbInaIfMacMaxReservationMsgLen.description: The default value for the Maximum_Reservation_Access_Message_Length in the Connect Message. This is the maximum length of a message that may be transmitted using a single reservation access. Any message greater than this should be transmitted by making multiple reservation requests. See also dvbInaIfConMaxReservationMsgLen.

dvbInaIfMacConnections.name: dvbInaIfMacConnections
dvbInaIfMacConnections.description: The number of connections currently active for this MAC entity.

dvbInaIfMacUnknownNiuError.name: dvbInaIfMacUnknownNiuError
dvbInaIfMacUnknownNiuError.description: This value is incremented if a message is received from a unknown NIU, except if it is a SignOn_Response Message.

dvbInaIfMacMsgDataError.name: dvbInaIfMacMsgDataError
dvbInaIfMacMsgDataError.description: This value is incremented if a MAC message is received with a data error, i.e. 1) is too short, 2) has an illegal Connection ID or Reservation ID, 3) is a reservation message from a NIU not reservation capable, 4) is a security message from a NIU not security capable 5) is an illegal MAC message.

dvbInaIfMacMsgHdrError.name: dvbInaIfMacMsgHdrError
dvbInaIfMacMsgHdrError.description: This value is incremented if a MAC message is received with a header error, i.e. 1) is too short, 2) does not contain a MAC address.

dvbInaIfMacInvalidNiu.name: dvbInaIfMacInvalidNiu
dvbInaIfMacInvalidNiu.description: This value is incremented if a MAC Initialisation Complete Message is transmitted with the Invalid_STB/NIU bit set.

dvbInaIfMacTimingRangingError.name: dvbInaIfMacTimingRangingError
dvbInaIfMacTimingRangingError.description: This value is incremented if a MAC Initialisation Complete Message is transmitted with the Timing_Ranging_Error bit set.

dvbInaIfMacPowerRangingError.name: dvbInaIfMacPowerRangingError
dvbInaIfMacPowerRangingError.description: This value is incremented if a MAC Initialisation Complete Message is transmitted with the Power_Ranging_Error bit set.

dvbInaIfMacOtherSignOnError.name: dvbInaIfMacOtherSignOnError
dvbInaIfMacOtherSignOnError.description: This value is incremented if a MAC Initialisation Complete Message is transmitted with the Other_Error bit set.

dvbInaIfProvChTable.name: dvbInaIfProvChTable
dvbInaIfProvChTable.description: This table specifies the information for the Default Configuration Message transmitted on the Provisioning channel.

dvbInaIfProvChEntry.name: dvbInaIfProvChEntry
dvbInaIfProvChEntry.description: An entry containing objects describing information for the Default Configuration Message transmitted on the Provisioning channel. More than one downstream can use than same entry or different entries can be made for different downstreams. If provisioning is done on an other INA, this table will be empty.

dvbInaIfProvChRowAccessStatus.name: dvbInaIfProvChRowAccessStatus
dvbInaIfProvChRowAccessStatus.description: Controls and reflects the status of this row in this table.

dvbInaIfProvChServiceChIfIndex.name: dvbInaIfProvChServiceChIfIndex
dvbInaIfProvChServiceChIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the upstream channel used as Service Channel for the provisioning.

dvbInaIfProvChBackupServiceChIfIndex.name: dvbInaIfProvChBackupServiceChIfIndex
dvbInaIfProvChBackupServiceChIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the upstream channel used as Backup Service Channel for the provisioning.

dvbInaIfProvChIncrPowerRetryCount.name: dvbInaIfProvChIncrPowerRetryCount
dvbInaIfProvChIncrPowerRetryCount.description: Specifies the number of attempts the NIU should do to enter the system at the same power level before incrementing its upstream transmit power for this MAC entity.

dvbInaIfProvChMaxPowerLevel.name: dvbInaIfProvChMaxPowerLevel
dvbInaIfProvChMaxPowerLevel.description: Specifies the maximum power in dBuV the NIU is allowed to transmit upstream for this MAC entity.

dvbInaIfProvChMinPowerLevel.name: dvbInaIfProvChMinPowerLevel
dvbInaIfProvChMinPowerLevel.description: Specifies the minimum power in dBuV the NIU has to transmit upstream for this MAC entity.

dvbInaIfProvChMaxBackOffExponent.name: dvbInaIfProvChMaxBackOffExponent
dvbInaIfProvChMaxBackOffExponent.description: Specifies the maximum back off exponent counter for this MAC entity.

dvbInaIfProvChMinBackOffExponent.name: dvbInaIfProvChMinBackOffExponent
dvbInaIfProvChMinBackOffExponent.description: Specifies the minimum back off exponent counter for this MAC entity.

dvbInaIfProvChAbsoluteTimeOffset.name: dvbInaIfProvChAbsoluteTimeOffset
dvbInaIfProvChAbsoluteTimeOffset.description: Specifies the default absolute time offset in 100 ns units to be used for first sign-on of a NIU for this MAC entity.

dvbInaIfDsChTable.name: dvbInaIfDsChTable
dvbInaIfDsChTable.description: This table describes the attributes of downstream channels (frequency bands).

dvbInaIfDsChEntry.name: dvbInaIfDsChEntry
dvbInaIfDsChEntry.description: List of attributes for a single Downstream channel. An entry in this table exists for each downstream ifEntry.

dvbInaIfDsChFrequency.name: dvbInaIfDsChFrequency
dvbInaIfDsChFrequency.description: The centre of the downstream frequency associated with this channel.

dvbInaIfDsChConnections.name: dvbInaIfDsChConnections
dvbInaIfDsChConnections.description: Specifies the number of connections currently active for this down stream channel.

dvbInaIfDsChTxPower.name: dvbInaIfDsChTxPower
dvbInaIfDsChTxPower.description: Specifies the down stream transmission power in dBuV of this interface.

dvbInaIfDsChDownCoaxId.name: dvbInaIfDsChDownCoaxId
dvbInaIfDsChDownCoaxId.description: Specifies the coax ID of the Downstream HFC segment to which the downstream channel is connected. By default this parameter is zero.

dvbInaIfDsChSymbolRate.name: dvbInaIfDsChSymbolRate
dvbInaIfDsChSymbolRate.description: Specifies the symbol rate for the Downstream channel.

dvbInaIfDsChModulation.name: dvbInaIfDsChModulation
dvbInaIfDsChModulation.description: Specifies the modulation for the Downstream channel.

dvbInaIfDsChType.name: dvbInaIfDsChType
dvbInaIfDsChType.description: Specifies if the Downstream channel is inband or out-of-band.

dvbInaIfDsChDefaultPID.name: dvbInaIfDsChDefaultPID
dvbInaIfDsChDefaultPID.description: The default value of the MPEG PID of the elementary stream that carries the data on this downstream. See also dvbInaIfConPID.

dvbInaIfDsChProvFrequency.name: dvbInaIfDsChProvFrequency
dvbInaIfDsChProvFrequency.description: Specifies the Downstream frequency of the provisioning channel. This setting is always used, no matter the provisioning channel is on this INA or on another. If the provisioning channel is on this INA, the value will be the frequency of one of the downstreams.

dvbInaIfDsChProvDownstreamType.name: dvbInaIfDsChProvDownstreamType
dvbInaIfDsChProvDownstreamType.description: Specifies the type of the downstream provisioning channel in the Provisioning Channel Message. 0 = QAM_MPEG, 1 = QPSK_1,544, 2 = QPSK_3,088 3..255 Reserved This setting is always used, no matter the provisioning channel is on this INA or on another. If the provisioning channel is on this INA, the value can be derived from the ib/oob type and modulation.

dvbInaIfDsChProvEnable.name: dvbInaIfDsChProvEnable
dvbInaIfDsChProvEnable.description: Specifies if this downstream channel is a Provisioning channel and as such transmits the Default Configuration Message. true = Provisioning channel false = not a Provisioning channel.

dvbInaIfDsChProvTableIndex.name: dvbInaIfDsChProvTableIndex
dvbInaIfDsChProvTableIndex.description: If this downstream channel is a provisioning channel, then an index to the Provisioning tabel must be give here.

dvbInaIfUsChTable.name: dvbInaIfUsChTable
dvbInaIfUsChTable.description: Describes the attributes of attached upstream channels (frequency bands).

dvbInaIfUsChEntry.name: dvbInaIfUsChEntry
dvbInaIfUsChEntry.description: List of attributes for a single upstream channel. The state of the upstream channel depends on the state of the MAC and downstream channel. If one of both or both are non-operational also the state upstream channel(s) shall be ready. That in the case of Space division Multiplex SDM each upstream channel has a different non-zero Coax ID.

dvbInaIfUsChFrequency.name: dvbInaIfUsChFrequency
dvbInaIfUsChFrequency.description: Specifies the frequency in Hz of the carrier used for this upstream channel.

dvbInaIfUsChSymbolRate.name: dvbInaIfUsChSymbolRate
dvbInaIfUsChSymbolRate.description: Specifies the symbol rate for this upstream channel.

dvbInaIfUsChModulation.name: dvbInaIfUsChModulation
dvbInaIfUsChModulation.description: Specifies the modulation for this upstream channel.

dvbInaIfUsChMacFlagSet.name: dvbInaIfUsChMacFlagSet
dvbInaIfUsChMacFlagSet.description: Specifies the MAC flag set assigned to this upstream channel.

dvbInaIfUsChId.name: dvbInaIfUsChId
dvbInaIfUsChId.description: Specifies the logical channel number associated with this upstream channel.

dvbInaIfUsChConnections.name: dvbInaIfUsChConnections
dvbInaIfUsChConnections.description: Specifies the number of connections currently active for this upstream channel.

dvbInaIfUsChCalibrationRxPower.name: dvbInaIfUsChCalibrationRxPower
dvbInaIfUsChCalibrationRxPower.description: Specifies the target receive signal power in dBuV to which the NIUs on this upstream channel are calibrated

dvbInaIfUsChUpCoaxId.name: dvbInaIfUsChUpCoaxId
dvbInaIfUsChUpCoaxId.description: Specifies the coax ID of the UpStream HFC segment to which the upstream channel is connected. By default this parameter is zero.

dvbInaIfUsChDownCoaxId.name: dvbInaIfUsChDownCoaxId
dvbInaIfUsChDownCoaxId.description: Specifies the coax ID of the Downstream HFC segment to which the upstream channel is connected. By default this parameter is zero.

dvbInaIfUsChAtmCells.name: dvbInaIfUsChAtmCells
dvbInaIfUsChAtmCells.description: Total number of recieved ATM Cells. 0 can indicate the counter is not supported.

dvbInaIfUsChAtmTimingErrors.name: dvbInaIfUsChAtmTimingErrors
dvbInaIfUsChAtmTimingErrors.description: Number of ATM Cells received with Timing Error. 0 can indicate the counter is not supported.

dvbInaIfUsChAtmPowerErrors.name: dvbInaIfUsChAtmPowerErrors
dvbInaIfUsChAtmPowerErrors.description: Number of ATM Cells received with Signal Level Error. 0 can indicate the counter is not supported.

dvbInaIfUsChAtmRSCorrectableErrors.name: dvbInaIfUsChAtmRSCorrectableErrors
dvbInaIfUsChAtmRSCorrectableErrors.description: Number of ATM Cells received with correctable Reed-Solomon Errors. 0 can indicate the counter is not supported.

dvbInaIfUsChAtmRSNonCorrectableErrors.name: dvbInaIfUsChAtmRSNonCorrectableErrors
dvbInaIfUsChAtmRSNonCorrectableErrors.description: Number of ATM Cells received with non-correctable Reed-Solomon Errors. 0 can indicate the counter is not supported.

dvbInaIfUsChAtmHecErrors.name: dvbInaIfUsChAtmHecErrors
dvbInaIfUsChAtmHecErrors.description: Number of ATM Cells received with HEC Error. 0 can indicate the counter is not supported.

dvbInaIfUsChAal5CrcErrors.name: dvbInaIfUsChAal5CrcErrors
dvbInaIfUsChAal5CrcErrors.description: Number AAL5 frames received with CRC error. 0 can indicate the counter is not supported.

dvbInaIfUsChAtmCollisionErrors.name: dvbInaIfUsChAtmCollisionErrors
dvbInaIfUsChAtmCollisionErrors.description: Number of ATM Cells received with Collision detected. 0 can indicate the counter is not supported.

dvbInaIfNiuTable.name: dvbInaIfNiuTable
dvbInaIfNiuTable.description: Describes the attributes of Network Interface Units.

dvbInaIfNiuEntry.name: dvbInaIfNiuEntry
dvbInaIfNiuEntry.description: Initially the table shall be empty. A new entry for a NIU is automatically created when the NIU in question signs on. Furthermore, the manager through the dvbInaIfNiuRowAccessStatus object can create new entries. This can be used in the case of re-provisioning where by the manager first makes an entry and sets all relevant parameters before the NIU is re-provisioned to this INA. When an entry is created for a NIU, also automatically an entry is created in the connection table for the default connection of the NIU in question. When a NIU entry is deleted, also all associated connection entries are deleted.

dvbInaIfNiuMacAddress.name: dvbInaIfNiuMacAddress
dvbInaIfNiuMacAddress.description: A 48-bit value representing the unique MAC address of the NIU.

dvbInaIfNiuRowAccessStatus.name: dvbInaIfNiuRowAccessStatus
dvbInaIfNiuRowAccessStatus.description: Controls and reflects the status of this row in this table.

dvbInaIfNiuState.name: dvbInaIfNiuState
dvbInaIfNiuState.description: Returned status information is the NIU status as assumed by the INA. The following states are possible: null(1) Any state other than below. ranging(2): The NIU has responded to a [MAC] Sign-on Request Message but the time ranging and power calibration is not yet complete. rangingAborted(3), The INA has sent a Initalisation Complete Message to the NIU with Completion_Status_Field != 0 rangingComplete(4), The INA has sent a Initalisation Complete Message to the NIU with Completion_Status_Field = 0 connecting(5), The INA has sent a Connect Message for first connection and is waiting for a Connect Response Message from the NIU. connectComplete(6) The INA has sent a Connect Confirm Message for first connection to the NIU. stopped(7) The NUI is in the stopped transmission state after the INA has send a Stop_Upstream_Transmission to the NIU and the NIU has returned a Link Management Response. NOTE: The INA only needs to report states it is able to detect.

dvbInaIfNiuDesiredState.name: dvbInaIfNiuDesiredState
dvbInaIfNiuDesiredState.description: Specifies the desired state of the NIU. This parameter can be set to one of the following values: down : Initial state. Disable NIU operation. start : Enable NIU operation. stop : Stop upstream transmission from the NIU.

dvbInaIfNiuDownIfIndex.name: dvbInaIfNiuDownIfIndex
dvbInaIfNiuDownIfIndex.description: Specifies the IfIndex of the downstream channel on which the NIU is tuned.

dvbInaIfNiuUpIfIndex.name: dvbInaIfNiuUpIfIndex
dvbInaIfNiuUpIfIndex.description: Specifies the IfIndex of the upstream channel that is used by the NIU.

dvbInaIfNiuUpTxLevel.name: dvbInaIfNiuUpTxLevel
dvbInaIfNiuUpTxLevel.description: Specifies the upstream transmit level. This is the INA notion of NIU transmit level. (See also 'dvbInaIfNiuRespTxLevel'.)

dvbInaIfNiuTimeOffset.name: dvbInaIfNiuTimeOffset
dvbInaIfNiuTimeOffset.description: Specifies the time offset. This is the INA notion of NIU time offset. (See also 'dvbInaIfNiuRespTimeOffset'.)

dvbInaIfNiuStatus.name: dvbInaIfNiuStatus
dvbInaIfNiuStatus.description: This 32-bit object specifies the status of this NIU. See <MAC> Sign-On Response Message and <MAC> Status Response Message [1] for the exact bit assignment. This object is updated after the reception of a <MAC> Status Response Message [1].

dvbInaIfNiuErrorCode.name: dvbInaIfNiuErrorCode
dvbInaIfNiuErrorCode.description: This 16-bit object specifies the error code in the <MAC> Sign-On Response Message. See ES 200 800 for the exact bit assignment.

dvbInaIfNiuRetryCount.name: dvbInaIfNiuRetryCount
dvbInaIfNiuRetryCount.description: This 8-bit object specifies the number of transmissions of the <MAC> Sign-On Response Message. (See [1]).

dvbInaIfNiuCapabilities.name: dvbInaIfNiuCapabilities
dvbInaIfNiuCapabilities.reference: See the [MAC] Sign-On Response Message in ES 200.800
dvbInaIfNiuCapabilities.description: This 32-bit object specifies the capabilities of this NIU. See also ES 200 800 for the bit assignment.

dvbInaIfNiuExtendedCapabilities.name: dvbInaIfNiuExtendedCapabilities
dvbInaIfNiuExtendedCapabilities.reference: See the [MAC] Sign-On Response Message in ES 200.800
dvbInaIfNiuExtendedCapabilities.description: This 32-bit object specifies the extended capabilities of this NIU. See also ES 200 800 and ECR 5 for the bit assignment.

dvbInaIfNiuInitCompletionStatus.name: dvbInaIfNiuInitCompletionStatus
dvbInaIfNiuInitCompletionStatus.description: This 8-bit object indicates the errors in the initialisation phase of this NIU. See the <MAC> Initialization Complete Message ES 200 800 for the exact bit assignment.

dvbInaIfNiuRequestStatus.name: dvbInaIfNiuRequestStatus
dvbInaIfNiuRequestStatus.description: This object triggers the transmission of a <MAC> Status Request Message [1]. This parameter can be set to one of the following parameters: 'NiuReqAddressPars(0)': request address parameters, 'NiuReqErrorPars(1)': request error parameters, 'NiuReqConnectionsPars(2)': request connection parameters, and 'NiuReqPhyLayerPars(3)': request physical layer parameters. When read this object returns 'NiuReqAddressPars(0)'.

dvbInaIfNiuResponseNumber.name: dvbInaIfNiuResponseNumber
dvbInaIfNiuResponseNumber.description: This object is incremented when a <MAC> Status Response Message [1] is received. This object can be polled to detect the reception of this message. After reset this object is zero.

dvbInaIfNiuRespTxLevel.name: dvbInaIfNiuRespTxLevel
dvbInaIfNiuRespTxLevel.description: Specifies the transmit power level of the NIU. This object is updated after the reception of a <MAC> Status Response Message [1] that is a response on the 'NiuReqPhyLayerPars(3)' request.

dvbInaIfNiuRespTimeOffset.name: dvbInaIfNiuRespTimeOffset
dvbInaIfNiuRespTimeOffset.description: Specifies the time offset of the NIU. This object is updated after the reception of a <MAC> Status Response Message [1] that is a response on the 'NiuReqPhyLayerPars(3)' request.

dvbInaIfNiuRespOoBDownFrequency.name: dvbInaIfNiuRespOoBDownFrequency
dvbInaIfNiuRespOoBDownFrequency.description: Specifies the OoB downstream frequency of the NIU. This object is updated after the reception of a <MAC> Status Response Message [1] that is a response on the 'NiuReqPhyLayerPars(3)' request.

dvbInaIfNiuRespIBDownFrequency.name: dvbInaIfNiuRespIBDownFrequency
dvbInaIfNiuRespIBDownFrequency.description: Specifies the IB downstream frequency of the NIU. This object is updated after the reception of a <MAC> Status Response Message [1] that is a response on the 'NiuReqPhyLayerPars(3)' request.

dvbInaIfNiuRespSNRLevel.name: dvbInaIfNiuRespSNRLevel
dvbInaIfNiuRespSNRLevel.description: Specifies the estimated SNR level at the RF input of the NIU. This object is updated after the reception of a <MAC> Status Response Message [1] that is a response on the 'NiuReqPhyLayerPars(3)' request.

dvbInaIfNiuRespRxLevel.name: dvbInaIfNiuRespRxLevel
dvbInaIfNiuRespRxLevel.description: Specifies the estimated downstream power level of the MAC messages at the RF input of the NIU. This object is updated after the reception of a <MAC> Status Response Message [1] that is a response on the 'NiuReqPhyLayerPars(3)' request.

dvbInaIfNiuDefaultConnectionId.name: dvbInaIfNiuDefaultConnectionId
dvbInaIfNiuDefaultConnectionId.description: Specifies the ConnectionId of the default connection that is assigned to this NIU.

dvbInaIfNiuLifetime.name: dvbInaIfNiuLifetime
dvbInaIfNiuLifetime.description: Defines how long after the NIU was signed off, the entry is removed from the table. An infinite(0) value would mean that the values are stored at least until the next reboot of the INA.

dvbInaIfNiuGrantProtocolTimeOut.name: dvbInaIfNiuGrantProtocolTimeOut
dvbInaIfNiuGrantProtocolTimeOut.description: The time that the NIU should wait before verifying the status of pending grants. Default value is dvbInaIfMacGrantProtocolTimeOut.

dvbInaIfNiuSlotConfigurationErr.name: dvbInaIfNiuSlotConfigurationErr
dvbInaIfNiuSlotConfigurationErr.description: NIU Error Parameter: Slot_Configuration_CRC_Error_Count, the number of errors in Slot_Configuration_Count R bytes, as found by the CRC decoder.

dvbInaIfNiuAtmPacketLoss.name: dvbInaIfNiuAtmPacketLoss
dvbInaIfNiuAtmPacketLoss.description: NIU Error Parameter: ATM_Packet_Loss_Count, the number of received ATM cells that were lost, either due to unrecoverable Reed-Solomon errors or because of an erroneous HEC of the ATM cell header.

dvbInaIfNiuSlEsCrcErr.name: dvbInaIfNiuSlEsCrcErr
dvbInaIfNiuSlEsCrcErr.description: Niu Error Parameter: SL-ESF_CRC_Error_Count, the number of CRC errors found in consecutive C1-C6.

dvbInaIfNiuSlEsFrameCount.name: dvbInaIfNiuSlEsFrameCount
dvbInaIfNiuSlEsFrameCount.description: NIU Error Parameter: SL-ESF_Frame_Count, the number of frames the statistics apply to.

dvbInaIfNiuSlotConfigurationCount.name: dvbInaIfNiuSlotConfigurationCount
dvbInaIfNiuSlotConfigurationCount.description: NIU Error Parameter: Slot_Configuration_Count, the number of R-byte sets (Rxa-Rxc) used to calculate Slot_Configuration_CRC_Error_Count.

dvbInaIfNiuRSErrCorrectable.name: dvbInaIfNiuRSErrCorrectable
dvbInaIfNiuRSErrCorrectable.description: NIU Error Parameter: Reed_Solomon_Errors_Correctable, MPEG frames received with correctable Reed-Solomon Errors (IB only).

dvbInaIfNiuRSErrNonCorrectable.name: dvbInaIfNiuRSErrNonCorrectable
dvbInaIfNiuRSErrNonCorrectable.description: NIU Error Parameter: Reed_Solomon_Errors_Non_Correctable, MPEG frames received with non-correctable Reed-Solomon Errors (IB only).

dvbInaIfNiuSignOnTime.name: dvbInaIfNiuSignOnTime
dvbInaIfNiuSignOnTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time this NIU was signed on. If the time is unknown, this value shall be zero.

dvbInaIfNiuDsChBytes.name: dvbInaIfNiuDsChBytes
dvbInaIfNiuDsChBytes.description: Number of bytes sent in direction INA to NIU.

dvbInaIfNiuUsChBytes.name: dvbInaIfNiuUsChBytes
dvbInaIfNiuUsChBytes.description: Number of bytes sent in direction NIU to INA. Includes backbone, NIU-to-NIU and broadcast/multicast traffic.

dvbInaIfNiuTimeRanging.name: dvbInaIfNiuTimeRanging
dvbInaIfNiuTimeRanging.description: Number of times the NIU has been time ranged.

dvbInaIfNiuPowerRanging.name: dvbInaIfNiuPowerRanging
dvbInaIfNiuPowerRanging.description: Number of times the NIU has been power ranged.

dvbInaIfConTable.name: dvbInaIfConTable
dvbInaIfConTable.description: Contains information about DVB-RC MAC connections.

dvbInaIfConEntry.name: dvbInaIfConEntry
dvbInaIfConEntry.description: Initially the table shall be empty. A new entry for a connection is automatically generated when a <MAC> Resource Request Message is received from the NIU in question requesting a new connection. Also during reprovisioning new entries are created. Furthermore, the manager through the dvbInaIfConAccessStatus object can create new entries. Connection table entries shall be deleted, when the associated NIU entry is deleted. Furthermore, the manager can delete unused connection entries. The following parameters can only be set when the connection is in state down(1) dvbInaIfConAccessStatus, dvbInaIfConEncapsulation, dvbInaIfConFilterMACAddress, dvbInaIfConPID.

dvbInaIfConNiuMacAddress.name: dvbInaIfConNiuMacAddress
dvbInaIfConNiuMacAddress.description: MAC address of the NIU that is associated with the connection.

dvbInaIfConConnectionId.name: dvbInaIfConConnectionId
dvbInaIfConConnectionId.description: Specifies the connection identifier to be used for this connection.

dvbInaIfConCurrentState.name: dvbInaIfConCurrentState
dvbInaIfConCurrentState.description: Current state of the connection. The following states are possible: down(1) In this state an entry is made in the connection table for the connection in question. However, there is not (yet) any connection on MAC layer between the INA and NIU. settingUp(2) Either the NIU in question has requested a connection via a [MAC] Resource Request message, or the manager has initiated a (new) connection by setting dvbInaConDesiredState to the state Up. up(3) In this state the connection in question is up and running. breakingDown(4) Either the NIU in question has requested to release the connection via a [MAC] Resource Request message, or the manager has initiated the release of the connection by setting dvbInaConDesiredState to the state: Down. downAlloc(5) In this state an entry is made in the connection table for the connection in question. Furthermore, the bandwidth for the fixed rate connection is allocated. However, the connection doesn't (yet) exist on MAC layer between the INA and NIU. alarm(6) The connection in question is in the alarm state. his means that either the parameter setting is not valid, or the scheduler of the MAC has not the resources to allocate the requested bandwidth for a fixed rate connection, or the NIU didn't response in time during the set-up of the connection or during the break down of it. This state shall be left, when either the manager sets dvbInaConDesiredState to Down(1) or, the NIU enters the Null(1) state.

dvbInaIfConDesiredState.name: dvbInaIfConDesiredState
dvbInaIfConDesiredState.description: Desired state for the connection. The following desired states are possible: down(1), up(3) and, downAlloc(5).

dvbInaIfConConnectionType.name: dvbInaIfConConnectionType
dvbInaIfConConnectionType.description: Specifies the kind of connection: fixed rate, contention based, or reservation based. This parameter can be set to a value that is an OR of the following bits: 'conTypeFixedRate(0)' 'conTypeContention(1)' 'conTypeReservation(2)' Default this object is 'conTypeContention(1)'.

dvbInaIfConAccessStatus.name: dvbInaIfConAccessStatus
dvbInaIfConAccessStatus.description: Controls and reflects the status of this row in this table.

dvbInaIfConEncapsulation.name: dvbInaIfConEncapsulation
dvbInaIfConEncapsulation.description: This object indicates the type of encapsulation provided on this connection. This object can have one of the following values: 'directIp(1)', 'ethernetMacBridging(2)', or 'ppp(3)'. By default this parameter is set to 'directIp(1)'.

dvbInaIfConAtmDownstreamVCC.name: dvbInaIfConAtmDownstreamVCC
dvbInaIfConAtmDownstreamVCC.description: ATM concatenated VPI and VCI Virtual Path Identifiers that is used for downstream OoB transmission.

dvbInaIfConAtmUpstreamVCC.name: dvbInaIfConAtmUpstreamVCC
dvbInaIfConAtmUpstreamVCC.description: ATM concatenated VPI and VCI Virtual Path Identifiers that is used for upstream transmission.

dvbInaIfConFilterMACAddress.name: dvbInaIfConFilterMACAddress
dvbInaIfConFilterMACAddress.description: Specifies the 'soft' MPEG MPE MAC address used to filter the data out of the downstream IB transmission. This is found in the Downstream_Multiprotocol_CBD substructure in the Connect Message.

dvbInaIfConPID.name: dvbInaIfConPID
dvbInaIfConPID.description: Specifies the MPEG PID of the elementary stream that carries the data.

dvbInaIfConMaxContentionMsgLen.name: dvbInaIfConMaxContentionMsgLen
dvbInaIfConMaxContentionMsgLen.description: The Maximum_Contention_Access_Message_Length in the Connect Message. This is the maximum length of a message that may be transmitted using contention access. Any message greater than this should use reservation access. The default value should be dvbInaIfMacMaxContentionMsgLen.

dvbInaIfConMaxReservationMsgLen.name: dvbInaIfConMaxReservationMsgLen
dvbInaIfConMaxReservationMsgLen.description: This is the maximum length of a message that may be transmitted using a single reservation access. Any message greater than this should be transmitted by making multiple reservation requests. The default value should be dvbInaIfMacMaxReservationMsgLen.

dvbInaIfConAuxFlags.name: dvbInaIfConAuxFlags
dvbInaIfConAuxFlags.description: The Connection_Control_Field_Aux from the Connect Message Structure. This is used to indicate if the Priority, Downstream flowspec and Session binding objects are used for the connection.

dvbInaIfConQosTable.name: dvbInaIfConQosTable
dvbInaIfConQosTable.description: Contains information about connection quality for DVB-RC MAC connections. Both upstream and downstream quality parameters are found.

dvbInaIfConQosEntry.name: dvbInaIfConQosEntry
dvbInaIfConQosEntry.description: An entry in the table is automatically created when a new entry in the connection table connection is created and the INA supports Quality of Service on the MAC layer. You must always create an entry in the Connection table first and this will automatically create an entry in the QoS table. The entries are deleted when the contection table entry is deleted.

dvbInaIfConQosPriority.name: dvbInaIfConQosPriority
dvbInaIfConQosPriority.description: The priority of the connection. Connections with low priority field value can be reprovisioned in order to accommodate the requirements of connections with high priority field. Standard data flow applications 0-79 Applications with QoS requirements 80-200 High priority applications 201-255

dvbInaIfConQosDsReqMaxPacketSize.name: dvbInaIfConQosDsReqMaxPacketSize
dvbInaIfConQosDsReqMaxPacketSize.description: A downstream QoS parameter. Defines the requested maximum packet size in the downstream. The parameter can be set either by the managment system, or by the INA according to the NIU resource request. The packet size includes propriety protocols header, transport protocol (UDP/TCP) header, and the IP header. The packet size does not include the Ethernet header.

dvbInaIfConQosDsReqBitrate.name: dvbInaIfConQosDsReqBitrate
dvbInaIfConQosDsReqBitrate.description: A downstream QoS parameter. Defines requested average bit rate in the downstream. The parameter can be set either by the managment system, or by the INA according to the NIU resource request.

dvbInaIfConQosDsReqJitter.name: dvbInaIfConQosDsReqJitter
dvbInaIfConQosDsReqJitter.description: A downstream QoS parameter. Defines the requested maximum allowed jitter in the downstream. The parameter can be set either by the managment system, or by the INA according to the NIU resource request.

dvbInaIfConQosDsAllocMaxPacketSize.name: dvbInaIfConQosDsAllocMaxPacketSize
dvbInaIfConQosDsAllocMaxPacketSize.description: A downstream QoS parameter. This is the actual maximum packet size supported by the INA in the downstream. The packet size includes propriety protocols header, transport protocol (UDP/TCP) header, and the IP header. The packet size does not include the Ethernet header.

dvbInaIfConQosDsAllocBitrate.name: dvbInaIfConQosDsAllocBitrate
dvbInaIfConQosDsAllocBitrate.description: A downstream QoS parameter. This is the actual average bit rate supported by the INA in the downstream.

dvbInaIfConQosDsAllocJitter.name: dvbInaIfConQosDsAllocJitter
dvbInaIfConQosDsAllocJitter.description: A downstream QoS parameter. This is the actual maximum jitter supported by the INA in the downstream.

dvbInaIfConQosUsReqBw.name: dvbInaIfConQosUsReqBw
dvbInaIfConQosUsReqBw.description: An upstream QoS parameter. The requested bandwidth for the upstream. The parameter can be set either by the managment system, or by the INA according to the NIU resource request.

dvbInaIfConQosUsReqMaxDistSlots.name: dvbInaIfConQosUsReqMaxDistSlots
dvbInaIfConQosUsReqMaxDistSlots.description: An upstream QoS parameter. The requested maximum distance between slots for the upstream. The parameter can be set either by the managment system, or by the INA according to the NIU resource request.

dvbInaIfConQosUsReqFrameLength.name: dvbInaIfConQosUsReqFrameLength
dvbInaIfConQosUsReqFrameLength.description: An upstream QoS parameter. The requested frame length for the upstream. The parameter can be set either by the managment system, or by the INA according to the NIU resource request.

dvbInaIfConQosUsAllocBw.name: dvbInaIfConQosUsAllocBw
dvbInaIfConQosUsAllocBw.description: An upstream QoS parameter. The actual allocated bandwidth for the upstream.

dvbInaIfConQosUsAllocMaxDistSlots.name: dvbInaIfConQosUsAllocMaxDistSlots
dvbInaIfConQosUsAllocMaxDistSlots.description: An upstream QoS parameter. The allocated distance between slots for the upstream. In case of using a cyclic assignment, this is the parameter sent by the INA in the connect message. In the case of reservation access, this parameter is an average number, calculated by the INA to reflect the actual allocation.

dvbInaIfConQosUsAllocFrameLength.name: dvbInaIfConQosUsAllocFrameLength
dvbInaIfConQosUsAllocFrameLength.description: An upstream QoS parameter. The allocated frame length for the upstream. In case of using a cyclic assignment, this is the parameter sent by the INA in the connect message. In the case of reservation access, this parameter is an average number, calculated by the INA to reflect the actual allocation.

dvbInaIfConQosUsReqFixedRateMethod.name: dvbInaIfConQosUsReqFixedRateMethod
dvbInaIfConQosUsReqFixedRateMethod.reference: ES 200 800 Connect Message and Resource Request Message
dvbInaIfConQosUsReqFixedRateMethod.description: An upstream QoS parameter. Request a specific fixed rate slot assignment method to be used. If cyclic then cyclic assignment is used. If slotList then the slot list method is used. The parameter can be set either by the managment system, or by the INA according to the NIU resource request. If the bit Cyclic_Assignment_Needed is set, the NIU requests the cyclic method. Otherwise the slot list method.

dvbInaIfConQosUsAllocFixedRateMethod.name: dvbInaIfConQosUsAllocFixedRateMethod
dvbInaIfConQosUsAllocFixedRateMethod.reference: ES 200 800 Connect Message and Resource Request Message
dvbInaIfConQosUsAllocFixedRateMethod.description: An upstream QoS parameter. Reflects the actual fixed rate slot assignment method that is used. If cyclic then cyclic assignment is used. If slotList then the slot list method is used.

dvbInaIfConSesTable.name: dvbInaIfConSesTable
dvbInaIfConSesTable.description: Contains information about session binding for DVB-RC MAC connections.

dvbInaIfConSesEntry.name: dvbInaIfConSesEntry
dvbInaIfConSesEntry.description: An entry in the table is automatically created when a new entry in the connection table connection is created if the INA and the NIU supports session binding. The entries are deleted when the contection table entry is deleted.

dvbInaIfConSesUsControl.name: dvbInaIfConSesUsControl
dvbInaIfConSesUsControl.description: Control which fields of the upstream session binding parameters that are used.

dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientSrcIpType.name: dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientSrcIpType
dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientSrcIpType.description: The type of the IP source address of the NIU client.

dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientSrcIp.name: dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientSrcIp
dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientSrcIp.description: The IP source address of the NIU client. Only used if bit 0 of dvbInaIfConSesUsControl is set.

dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientDstIpType.name: dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientDstIpType
dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientDstIpType.description: The type of the IP destination address of the NIU client.

dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientDstIp.name: dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientDstIp
dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientDstIp.description: The IP destination address of the NIU client. Only used if bit 1 of dvbInaIfConSesUsControl is set.

dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientSrcPort.name: dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientSrcPort
dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientSrcPort.description: The source port of the NIU client. Only used if bit 2 of dvbInaIfConSesUsControl is set.

dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientDstPort.name: dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientDstPort
dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientDstPort.description: The destination port of the NIU client. Only used if bit 3 of dvbInaIfConSesUsControl is set.

dvbInaIfConSesUsTransportProtocol.name: dvbInaIfConSesUsTransportProtocol
dvbInaIfConSesUsTransportProtocol.description: The transport protocol used by the NIU client (UDP/TCP). This is the 8-bit protocol field in the IP header. Only used if bit 4 of dvbInaIfConSesUsControl is set.

dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientSrcMac.name: dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientSrcMac
dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientSrcMac.description: The Ethernet source MAC address of the NIU client. Only used if bit 5 of dvbInaIfConSesUsControl is set.

dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientDstMac.name: dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientDstMac
dvbInaIfConSesUsNiuClientDstMac.description: The Ethernet destination MAC address of the NIU client. Only used if bit 6 of dvbInaIfConSesUsControl is set.

dvbInaIfConSesUsEthernetProtocol.name: dvbInaIfConSesUsEthernetProtocol
dvbInaIfConSesUsEthernetProtocol.description: The ethernet protocol, as described in the ethernet header. This is the type field in the Ethernet protocol header. Only used if bit 7 of dvbInaIfConSesUsControl is set.

dvbInaIfConSesUsSessionId.name: dvbInaIfConSesUsSessionId
dvbInaIfConSesUsSessionId.description: The session_Id, as defined for PPPoE protocol. Only used if bit 8 of dvbInaIfConSesUsControl is set.

dvbInaIfConSesDsControl.name: dvbInaIfConSesDsControl
dvbInaIfConSesDsControl.description: Control which fields of the downstream session binding parameters that are used.

dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientSrcIpType.name: dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientSrcIpType
dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientSrcIpType.description: The type of the IP source address of the INA client.

dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientSrcIp.name: dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientSrcIp
dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientSrcIp.description: The IP source address of the INA client. Only used if bit 0 of dvbInaIfConSesDsControl is set.

dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientDstIpType.name: dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientDstIpType
dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientDstIpType.description: The type of the IP destination address of the INA client.

dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientDstIp.name: dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientDstIp
dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientDstIp.description: The IP destination address of the INA client. Only used if bit 1 of dvbInaIfConSesDsControl is set.

dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientSrcPort.name: dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientSrcPort
dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientSrcPort.description: The source port of the INA client. Only used if bit 2 of dvbInaIfConSesDsControl is set.

dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientDstPort.name: dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientDstPort
dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientDstPort.description: The destination port of the INA client. Only used if bit 3 of dvbInaIfConSesDsControl is set.

dvbInaIfConSesDsTransportProtocol.name: dvbInaIfConSesDsTransportProtocol
dvbInaIfConSesDsTransportProtocol.description: The transport protocol used by the INA client (UDP/TCP). This is the 8-bit protocol field in the IP header. Only used if bit 4 of dvbInaIfConSesDsControl is set.

dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientSrcMac.name: dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientSrcMac
dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientSrcMac.description: The Ethernet source MAC address of the INA client. Only used if bit 5 of dvbInaIfConSesDsControl is set.

dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientDstMac.name: dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientDstMac
dvbInaIfConSesDsInaClientDstMac.description: The Ethernet destination MAC address of the INA client. Only used if bit 6 of dvbInaIfConSesDsControl is set.

dvbInaIfConSesDsEthernetProtocol.name: dvbInaIfConSesDsEthernetProtocol
dvbInaIfConSesDsEthernetProtocol.description: The ethernet protocol, as described in the ethernet header. This is the type field in the Ethernet protocol header. Only used if bit 7 of dvbInaIfConSesDsControl is set.

dvbInaIfConSesDsSessionId.name: dvbInaIfConSesDsSessionId
dvbInaIfConSesDsSessionId.description: The session_Id, as defined for PPPoE protocol. Only used if bit 8 of dvbInaIfConSesDsControl is set.

dvbInaIfConHdrSupTable.name: dvbInaIfConHdrSupTable
dvbInaIfConHdrSupTable.description: Table contains information about the header suppression for a connection, indexed trough the Connection ID and the Context ID.

dvbInaIfConHdrSupEntry.name: dvbInaIfConHdrSupEntry
dvbInaIfConHdrSupEntry.description: An entry in the table is automatically generated when a new header suppression starts. Or when a reprovisioning is made. An entry is deleted when the connection is deleted.

dvbInaIfConHdrSupContextId.name: dvbInaIfConHdrSupContextId
dvbInaIfConHdrSupContextId.description: The context ID for the header suppression session.

dvbInaIfConHdrSupDirection.name: dvbInaIfConHdrSupDirection
dvbInaIfConHdrSupDirection.description: The direction for this the header suppression session.

dvbInaIfConHdrSupControl.name: dvbInaIfConHdrSupControl
dvbInaIfConHdrSupControl.description: String of bits that control the use of the header suppression. Each of the first 103 bits, indicates if a byte in the header is suppressed or not. Bit 103 is used as an overall suppression enable. If a mask bit is 0, the matching header byte is suppressed. If bit 103 is set, suppression is performed. Bit 103 is the least significant bit in octet 13. See also dvbInaIfConHdrSupHeader.

dvbInaIfConHdrSupGeneration.name: dvbInaIfConHdrSupGeneration
dvbInaIfConHdrSupGeneration.description: The generation number that is attached to the header fields value.

dvbInaIfConHdrSupHeaderLength.name: dvbInaIfConHdrSupHeaderLength
dvbInaIfConHdrSupHeaderLength.description: The number of usefull bytes in the suppression header. This is the number of the last zero in the dvbInaIfConHdrSupControl.

dvbInaIfConHdrSupHeader.name: dvbInaIfConHdrSupHeader
dvbInaIfConHdrSupHeader.description: The header used for header suppression. Both fixed and changing fields together. Only the first dvbInaIfConHdrSupHeaderLength is used.

dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuTable.name: dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuTable
dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuTable.description: The table describes information created on INA 1 for a NIU that is about to be reprovisioned.

dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuEntry.name: dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuEntry
dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuEntry.description: An entry in the table is created by the manager when a NIU is about to be reprovisioned. When the reprovisioning is done and the NIU entry is deleted after dvbInaIfNiuLifetime this entry will be deleted too.

dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuRowAccessStatus.name: dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuRowAccessStatus
dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuRowAccessStatus.description: Controls and reflects the status of this row in this table.

dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuCommand.name: dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuCommand
dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuCommand.description: Controls the reprovisioning on INA 1. When set to reprovStart the actual reporvisioning on INA 1 is initiated with a Reprovisioning Message to the NIU. Everything must be prepared for the reprovisioning when this is done. When read the response will always be reprovIdle.

dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuDsChFrequency.name: dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuDsChFrequency
dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuDsChFrequency.description: The centre of the new downstream frequency when the NIU is reprovisioned to INA 2.

dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuDsChSymbolRate.name: dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuDsChSymbolRate
dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuDsChSymbolRate.description: Specifies the new symbol rate for the Downstream channel when the NIU is reprovisioned.

dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuDsChModulation.name: dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuDsChModulation
dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuDsChModulation.description: Specifies the new modulation for the Downstream channel when the NIU is reprovisioned.

dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuDsChType.name: dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuDsChType
dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuDsChType.description: Specifies if the new Downstream channel is inband or out-of-band when the NIU is reprovisioned.

dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuUsChFrequency.name: dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuUsChFrequency
dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuUsChFrequency.description: Specifies the new upstream channel frequency in Hz when the NIU is reprovisoned.

dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuUsChSymbolRate.name: dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuUsChSymbolRate
dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuUsChSymbolRate.description: Specifies the new upstream channel symbol rate when the NIU is reprovisoned.

dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuUsChModulation.name: dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuUsChModulation
dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuUsChModulation.description: Specifies the new upstream modulation when the NIU is reprovisoned.

dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuUsChId.name: dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuUsChId
dvbInaIfReprovSrcNiuUsChId.description: Specifies the new logical channel number associated with the upstream channel when the NIU is reprovisioned.

dvbInaIfReprovDstNiuTable.name: dvbInaIfReprovDstNiuTable
dvbInaIfReprovDstNiuTable.description: The table describes information created on INA 2 for a NIU that is about to be reprovisioned.

dvbInaIfReprovDstNiuEntry.name: dvbInaIfReprovDstNiuEntry
dvbInaIfReprovDstNiuEntry.description: An entry in the table is created by the manager when a NIU is about to be reprovisioned. When the reprovisioning is done and the NIU signs on to INA 2 the information is transfered to the NIU table and the entry in this table is deleted automatically.

dvbInaIfReprovDstNiuMacAddress.name: dvbInaIfReprovDstNiuMacAddress
dvbInaIfReprovDstNiuMacAddress.description: A 48-bit value representing the unique MAC address of the NIU to be reprovisioned. This is the index of the table.

dvbInaIfReprovDstNiuRowAccessStatus.name: dvbInaIfReprovDstNiuRowAccessStatus
dvbInaIfReprovDstNiuRowAccessStatus.description: Controls and reflects the status of this row in this table.

dvbInaIfReprovDstNiuCommand.name: dvbInaIfReprovDstNiuCommand
dvbInaIfReprovDstNiuCommand.description: Controls the reprovisioning on INA 2. When set to reprovPrepare INA 2 will generate the necessary information that needs to be transferred back to INA 1. This includes: New Connection ID's New PID for each connection New downstream VPI/VCI New upstream VPI/VCI New upstream number Furthermore new fixed rate parameters are calculated if one of the new connections are fixed rate. All settings needed to calculate these new parameters must be given before reprovPrepare is set. When set to reprovReceiveNiu this is an indication to INA 2 that the NIU is expected to sign-on now. When read the response will always be reprovIdle.
